Corn Relish Salad

3/4 cup sugar
1/2 cup CRISCO~ Oil
1/4 cup white vinegar
1/2 teaspoon celery seed
1/4 teaspoon whole mustard seed

1 can (17 ounces) whole kernel corn, drained

1 can (16 ounces) sauerkraut, pressed to remove excess liquid 1/2 cup 
chopped green pepper
1/3 cup chopped onion

1 jar (2 ounces) diced pimiento, drained

Combine sugar, Crisco~ Oil, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed in medium 
serving bowl. Stir until sugar
dissolves. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate at 
least 8 hours or overnight. Drain and
stir before serving.

6 to 8 servings.
